=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_SinOsc_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 751 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 750.7504
  harmonic_decay_rate: -10.0071
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5625
  pitch_clarity: 93.2323
  inharmonicity: 0.5478
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -10.3544
  resonance_freq: 818.2617

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: SinOsc Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/SinOsc.html
// Tags: SinOsc, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// create an audio-rate sine wave at 200 Hz,
// starting with phase 0 and an amplitude of 0.5
{ SinOsc.ar(200, 0, 0.5) }.play;

// modulate the frequency with an exponential ramp
{ SinOsc.ar(XLine.kr(2000, 200), 0, 0.5) }.play;

// more complex frequency modulation
{ SinOsc.ar(SinOsc.ar(XLine.kr(1, 1000, 9), 0, 200, 800), 0, 0.25) }.play;

// phase modulation (see also PMOsc)
{ SinOsc.ar(800, SinOsc.ar(XLine.kr(1, 1000, 9), 0, 2pi), 0.25) }.play;
